From 0972e474a057bbfe03a1995916dd976f319e01aa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sean Smith <DefendTheDisabled@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 16:00:34 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 10/16] ntfs3: preserve ptime across rename-over
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements rename-over preservation for ntfs3, mirroring the
Btrfs approach but using i_crtime directly (since ntfs3 maps
ptime to NTFS Date Created).

When atomic save creates a new file and renames it over an
existing file, normally the new file has a fresh crtime (the
time of the temp file creation). This silently destroys the
original file's creation date — the exact scenario ptime is
designed to prevent.

Fix: in ntfs_rename, when the target exists, save the target's
i_crtime before replacing it, then apply the saved value to the
new inode's i_crtime. Matches Windows behavior where File
Explorer and PowerShell Move-Item preserve the target's
creation time.

Guards: only regular files with nlink=1, excludes
RENAME_EXCHANGE and RENAME_WHITEOUT.

Ref: Decision #51 (rename-over preservation on all 5 filesystems)
Files: fs/ntfs3/namei.c:ntfs_rename
---
 fs/ntfs3/namei.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/ntfs3/namei.c b/fs/ntfs3/namei.c
index b2af8f695e60..40d06884fac7 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs3/namei.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs3/namei.c
@@ -292,6 +292,16 @@ static int ntfs_rename(struct mnt_idmap *idmap, struct inode *dir,
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 
+	/* ptime rename-over: save target creation time before unlink */
+	struct timespec64 saved_crtime = {};
+	bool inherit_crtime = false;
+
+	if (new_inode && S_ISREG(inode->i_mode) &&
+	    S_ISREG(new_inode->i_mode) && inode->i_nlink == 1) {
+		saved_crtime = ntfs_i(new_inode)->i_crtime;
+		inherit_crtime = true;
+	}
+
 	if (new_inode) {
 		/* Target name exists. Unlink it. */
 		dget(new_dentry);
@@ -330,6 +340,10 @@ static int ntfs_rename(struct mnt_idmap *idmap, struct inode *dir,
 
 	err = ni_rename(dir_ni, new_dir_ni, ni, de, new_de);
 	if (!err) {
+		/* ptime rename-over: inherit target creation time */
+		if (inherit_crtime)
+			ni->i_crtime = saved_crtime;
+
 		simple_rename_timestamp(dir, dentry, new_dir, new_dentry);
 		mark_inode_dirty(inode);
 		mark_inode_dirty(dir);
-- 
